b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48476.htm)  [Next](sbe48478.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n30\\. This is said in Sm _ri_ ti also.\n\nThat for those as well who know Brahman, as for others, the eating of food of\nany kind is lawful only in case of extreme need, Sm _ri_ ti also declares, 'He\nwho being in danger of his life eats food from anywhere is stained by sin no\nmore than the lotus leaf by water.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 31. ... as to non-proceeding according to liking](sbe48478.htm)\n\n"